Heat grill. Mix brown sugar, chili powder and salt in small bowl. Pat pork tenderloin dry; rub with spice mixture. Brush pineapple with oil. Place tenderloin on grill over indirect heat. Cover and cook 20 minutes on each side until pork reaches 160 degrees F. on instant-read thermometer. Add pineapple to grill during last 5 minutes of grilling, turning once. Let pork stand for 5 minutes. Meanwhile, heat sauce in small microwavable bowl on High for 20 to 30 seconds or until heated through. Cut tenderloin into 1/2-inch slices; arrange on serving platter with pineapple. Drizzle with warm sauce.